desired state and actual state
desired state: the state that we want to be in
actual state: the state that we are currently in
the goal of devops is to make the actual state match the desired state
desired state = actual state

terraform.tfstate file: a file that contains the actual state of the infrastructure
remote backend : a way to store the terraform.tfstate file in a remote location (e.g. s3, azure blob storage, etc.)
store state file to remote backend
donot update or delete the file
and state locking and isolation of statefile
regularly backup the state file
state locking: a mechanism to prevent multiple users from modifying the state file at the same time